	"description": "To build mastery in software development, you should build projects.\n\nNot one. \n\nNot two. \n\nLots of projects!\n\nBut you have to start right. If you jump into any random project as a beginner\nor junior developer, you&#x27;ll not only feel lost, you&#x27;ll begin to doubt if\nprogramming is for you. So work smart. \n\nStart small.\n\nFirst, build your confidence from one tiny project. Then another tiny project.\nAfter multiple small projects, move on to something bigger, and go as big as\nyour imagination allows.\n\n",
